****************************************************************
*                                                              *
* Directions for compiling TOF calibration software packages   *
*                                                              *
*  Joe Santoro                                                 *
*  9-6-01                                                      *
*                                                              *
****************************************************************



Use Makefile_map if you want to link into the old Mapfile libraries. This will force the executable
to use the old mapfile to read in the calibration constants.

|------------------------------------------------------|
| To make all the executables in this directory, type: |
|                                                      |
| make -f Makefile_map.mk all                          |
|------------------------------------------------------|



Use Makefile_caldb if you want to link into the Calibration Database libs. This will force the
executable to use the CalDB to read in the calibration constants. 

|------------------------------------------------------|
| To make all the executables in this directory, type: |
|                                                      |
| make -f Makefile_caldb.mk all                        |
|------------------------------------------------------|
